{"title_page": "Spoons sex position", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n[[File:Wiki-spoons-sp.png|thumb|The spoons position in sex]]\n{{short description|Sex position resembling spoons that may be positioned side by side, with bowls aligned}}\nThe '''spoons position''' or '''spooning''' is a [[Sex positions|sexual position]] and a [[Hug|cuddling]] technique. The name derives from the way that two [[spoon]]s may be positioned side by side, with bowls aligned.<ref>Cox, Tracey. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=cIyu5x_7vrYC&printsec=frontcover The Hot Sex Handbook]'' (Random House, Inc., 2005), p. 64.</ref> The sexual spoons position is a form of a rear-entry position, the other being the [[doggy style]] position.<ref name=\"Kar\">{{cite book |authors=Nilamadhab Kar, Gopal Chandra Kar| title = Comprehensive Textbook of Sexual Medicine | publisher = [[Jaypee Brothers| Jaypee Brothers Publishers]]|pages=110\u2013111| isbn = 8180614050|year=2005| accessdate = February 10, 2014 | url =https://books.google.com/books?id=YxcjMPbGHQIC&pg=PA110}}</ref> The spoons sex position has been called one of the \"basic four\" sex positions.<ref>Tim F. LaHaye, Beverly LaHaye, Mike Yorkey. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=O33loW9EUbEC&printsec=frontcover The Act of Marriage After 40: Making Love for Life]'' (Zondervan, 2000), pp. 92-93.</ref>have sex the best way\n\n==Practice==\nIn the spoons cuddling position, one partner lies on one side with knees bent while the other partner lies with his or her front pressed against their back. The spoons cuddling position is not limited to two people.\n\nIn the sex position, the receiving partner would be in the inner spoon position and the penetrator is in the outer spoon in preparation for rear-entry penetration. For penetration, the partners may separate their upper bodies, with just the pelvises connecting, and their legs can also rest on top of each other.<ref>Castleman, Michael. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=ZsgwgoKndqwC&printsec=frontcover Great Sex: A Man's Guide to the Secret Principles of Total-Body Sex]'' (Rodale, 2004), p. 143.</ref> The receiving partner may lift the upper knee to allow for easier penetration.<ref name=\"Locker\">Locker, Sari. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=cwyRGw7xSCAC&printsec=frontcover The Complete Idiot's Guide to Amazing Sex]'' (Penguin, 2005), pp. 194-195.</ref>\n\nDuring heterosexual sexual activity, the penetrating partner can caress the woman's [[stomach]] and stimulate her [[breast]]s, the back of the neck and ears, and [[clitoris]]. The woman can stimulate her own clitoris or her partner's [[scrotum]].<ref name=\"Foley\">Sallie Foley, Sally A. Kope, Dennis P. Sugrue. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=krp6AF8ruuAC&printsec=frontcover Sex Matters for Women: A Complete Guide to Taking Care of Your Sexual Self]'' (Guilford Press, 2001), pp. 238-239.</ref> In addition, the [[Human penis|penis]] stimulates the front of the [[vagina]], and may stimulate an area that is commonly termed ''the [[G-spot]]''.<!--NOTE: The words \"commonly termed\" are used because the G-spot has never been proven to definitively exist, and women vary in their reports of its existence.--><ref name=\"Rosenau\">Rosenau, Douglas E. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=uHIsvrnnvPkC&printsec=frontcover A Celebration of Sex]'' (Thomas Nelson Inc, 2002), p. 147.</ref> Along with the [[doggy style]] position, this may be the best position from which to stimulate this area.<ref>Stefan Bechtel, Larry Stains, Laurence Roy Stains. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=FWtcUwVsMkcC&printsec=frontcover Sex: A Man's Guide]'' (Rodale, 1996), p. 100.</ref><ref>Keesling, Barbara. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=EG2qGvbgneoC&printsec=frontcover Sexual Pleasure: Reaching New Heights of Sexual Arousal and Intimacy]'' (Hunter House, 2005), p. 101.</ref>\n\nVariations on this position include the partners lying on their sides face-to-face or in the scissors position.<ref name=\"Kalish\">Kalish, Nancy. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=KvmknG0zTM8C&printsec=frontcover The Nice Girl's Guide to Sensational Sex]'' (iUniverse, 2003), p. 182.</ref> [[Anal sex]] is also possible in this position, along with use of a [[Vibrator (sex toy)|vibrator]].<ref>Taormino, Tristan. ''[https://www.facebook.com/180979668987203/videos/181088912309612/ Down and Dirty Sex Secrets: The New and Naughty Guide to Being Great in Bed]'' (HarperCollins, 2003), p. 143.</ref><ref name=\"Heiman\"/>\n\n==Advantages and disadvantages==\nThe spoons position allows for a great deal of [[physical intimacy]], as there is full-body contact which allows for cuddling.<ref name=\"Heiman\">Julia Heiman, Joseph Lopiccolo, David Palladini. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=A_p-dLUcvPYC&printsec=frontcover Becoming Orgasmic: A Sexual and Personal Growth Program for Women]'' (Simon and Schuster, 1987), p. 203.</ref> Both partners have control of the angle and depth of penetration, and slow, low-intensity sex can last for a long time because it usually takes longer for the man to reach [[orgasm]].<ref>Salinger, Eve. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=-rcSntK98D4C&printsec=frontcover The Complete Idiot's Guide to Pleasing Your Man]'' (Penguin, 2005).</ref> However, there is little visual stimulation for either partner, as they are not facing one another and cannot see each other's bodies fully. The penis can also slip out easily.<ref name=\"Foley\"/>\n\nThe spoons position may be preferred by couples who have just woken up or are very tired. It may be used if the woman is [[Pregnancy|pregnant]], even during the last trimester, because it does not put any pressure on the [[abdomen]].<ref name=\"Kalish\"/> It is also good for those recovering from illness or surgery, or the elderly, because it puts less strain on muscles.<ref name=\"Locker\"/><ref name=\"Rosenau\"/>\n\n==History==\nMost Roman [[erotic art]] depicted couples in the spoons position.<ref>Younger, John Grimes. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=IEqPs2Toy7YC&printsec=frontcover Sex in the Ancient World from A to Z]'' (Psychology Press, 2005), p. 124.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite book|author=Jean Rogiere| title=The Little Book of Sex| publisher=Ulysses Press| year=2001| isbn=1-56975-305-9| page=96}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons category-inline|Spooning positions}}\n\n{{Sex}}\n{{Sex positions}}\n\n[[Category:Sex positions]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n[[File:Wiki-spoons-sp.png|thumb|The spoons position in sex]]\n{{short description|Sex position resembling spoons that may be positioned side by side, with bowls aligned}}\nThe '''spoons position''' or '''spooning''' is a [[Sex positions|sexual position]] and a [[Hug|cuddling]] technique. The name derives from the way that two [[spoon]]s may be positioned side by side, with bowls aligned.<ref>Cox, Tracey. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=cIyu5x_7vrYC&printsec=frontcover The Hot Sex Handbook]'' (Random House, Inc., 2005), p. 64.</ref> The sexual spoons position is a form of a rear-entry position, the other being the [[doggy style]] position.<ref name=\"Kar\">{{cite book |authors=Nilamadhab Kar, Gopal Chandra Kar| title = Comprehensive Textbook of Sexual Medicine | publisher = [[Jaypee Brothers| Jaypee Brothers Publishers]]|pages=110\u2013111| isbn = 8180614050|year=2005| accessdate = February 10, 2014 | url =https://books.google.com/books?id=YxcjMPbGHQIC&pg=PA110}}</ref> The spoons sex position has been called one of the \"basic four\" sex positions.<ref>Tim F. LaHaye, Beverly LaHaye, Mike Yorkey. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=O33loW9EUbEC&printsec=frontcover The Act of Marriage After 40: Making Love for Life]'' (Zondervan, 2000), pp. 92-93.</ref>\n\n==Practice==\nIn the spoons cuddling position, one partner lies on one side with knees bent while the other partner lies with his or her front pressed against their back. The spoons cuddling position is not limited to tw