eopards F.C.|Black Leopards]]\n|21||11||5||5||33||21||+12||'''38'''||Qualification for PSL promotion play-offs\n|-\n||3||align=\"left\"|[[University of Pretoria F.C.|University of Pretoria]]\n|21||10||7||4||29||18||+11||'''37'''\n|-\n||4||align=\"left\"|[[F.C. AK]]\n|21||7||6||8||27||24||+3||'''27'''\n|-\n||5||align=\"left\"|[[Witbank Spurs]]\n|21||6||6||9||22||26||-4||'''24'''\n|-\n||6||align=\"left\"|[[Dynamos F.C. (South Africa)|Dynamos]]\n|21||6||3||12||21||37||-16||'''21'''\n|-\n||7||align=\"left\"|[[United FC (South Africa)|United]]\n|21||6||5||10||17||24||-7||'''20'''\n|- style=\"background:#FFCCCC;\"\n||8||align=\"left\"|[[Batau F.C.|Batau]]\n|21||4||3||14||31||45||-14||'''15'''||Relegation to the [[Vodacom League]]\n|}\n\n<small>Updated 8 May 2011:<ref name=\"TableStandings\"/><ref name=\"2010/11 Log\"/></small>\n\n'''Note:''' Pretoria University initially won 2nd place in the Inland stream, due to a 3p penalty hitting Black Leopards, for fielding an unregistered player at one of their victories in the spring. Few days later the penalty was however reverted, as Black Leopards managed to win the appeal case. The log therefore ended to award the second place for Black Leopards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/21804/black-leopards-look-set-for-psl-promotional-playoffs.php|title=Black Leopards look set for PSL promotional playoffs -Leopards win appeal against PSL ruling \n|author=KickOff|date=2011-05-17}}</ref>\n\n===Post Season===\n\n====NFD Final====\nThe winner of the two streams, [[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]] and [[Jomo Cosmos]] will meet and play a two legged tie, on May 14 and May 22, to determine the overall 2010-11 NFD championship. The NFD champion will gain an automatic promotion to the [[Premier Soccer League|PSL]]. While the looser of the NFD Final will get a second chance to promote to PSL, at the Promotion Play Offs.\n\n{{TwoLeg start}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]]|ZAF| 0\u20130<br>(penalty 4\u20135) |'''[[Jomo Cosmos]]'''|ZAF| 0\u20130 <br>[http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D417426 report] | 0\u20130 <br>[http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D418438 report]}}\n|}\n\n====Promotion play offs====\nThe losing team of the NFD Final ([[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]]), together with both runnerups of the NFD streams ([[Thanda Royal Zulu FC|Thanda Royal Zulu]] and [[Black Leopards F.C.|Black Leopards]]), and finally the second lowest ranked team of PSL ([[Vasco da Gama (South Africa)|Vasco da Gama]]), entered into the Promotion play offs. This play off competition, was played as a cup with two legged matches, with an unseeded draw to decide the fixtures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/21643/first-division-promotional-play-off-draw-held.php|title=NFD Play-off draw completed|author=KickOff|date=2011-05-09}}</ref>\nThe two semifinals were scheduled to be played simultaneously at May 25 and 29. Due to Black Leopards having qualified for the [[2011 Nedbank Cup]] final at May 28, the two semifinals were however rescheduled, to be played at June 8 and 11. A two legged final with the two winning teams from the semifinal, was played on June 15 and 18.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp?id=418141|title=Leopards change play-off fixture|author=PSL|date=2011-05-20|access-date=2011-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314015859/http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp?id=418141|archive-date=2012-03-14|url-status=dead}}</ref> Only the winner of the Promotion play off final was get promoted to play the next season in PSL.\n\n'''Semifinals:'''\n{{TwoLeg start}}\n{{TwoLegResult|'''[[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]]'''|ZAF | 4\u20131 | [[Thanda Royal Zulu FC|Thanda Royal Zulu]]|ZAF |0\u20130 <br>[http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D420551 report]|4\u20131 <br>[http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D420987 report]}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[Vasco da Gama (South Africa)|Vasco da Gama]]|ZAF |2\u20134| '''[[Black Leopards F.C.|Black Leopards]]'''|ZAF |1\u20131<br>[http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D420587 report] |1\u20133<br>[http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D420953 report]}}\n|}\n\n'''Promotion Play Off Final:'''\n{{TwoLeg start}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]]|ZAF |0\u20132 | '''[[Black Leopards F.C.|Black Leopards]]'''|ZAF | 0\u20130 <br> [http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D421493 report] | 0\u20132<br>[http://www.psl.co.za/article.asp%3Fid%3D421807 report] }}\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100323132320/http://www.psl.co.za/first.asp PSL.co.za]\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{South African soccer seasons}}\n{{2010-11 in African Football (CAF)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2010-11 National First Division}}\n[[Category:National First Division seasons]]\n[[Category:2010\u201311 in African second tier association football leagues|South]]\n[[Category:2010\u201311 in South African soccer leagues]]\n\n[[pt:Temporada 2010-11 da PSL]]\n", "text_old": "{{ infobox football league season\n| image                      = \n| caption                    = \n| competition                = [[National First Division]]\n| season                     = 2010\u201311 \n| winners                    = \n| promoted                   = \n| relegated                  = \n| matches                    =\n| total goals                =\n| average goals              =\n| league topscorer           =\n| biggest home win           =\n| biggest away win           =\n| highest scoring            =\n| longest wins               =\n| longest unbeaten           =\n| longest winless            =\n| longest losses             =\n| highest attendance         =\n| lowest attendance          =\n| average attendance         =\n| prevseason                 = [[2009\u201310 National First Division|2009\u201310]]\n| nextseason                 = [[2011\u201312 National First Division|2011\u201312]]\n}}\n\n'''2010\u201311 National First Division''', was the season from September 2010 until May 2011, of South Africa's second tier of professional [[association football|football]]. The overall NFD champion was promoted to the first level, known as [[Premier Soccer League]] (PSL). While the losing team of the championship final, faced a round robin playoff stage, against the second lowest ranked team of PSL and the two second ranked teams of the NFD streams.\n\n==Season Structure==\nThe league is made up of 16 teams, split into 2 streams. Each team plays the other 7 teams in their stream 3 times, for a total of 21 games. Teams receive 3 points for a win, 1 for draw, and 0 for a loss. At the end of the season, the top ranked team from each stream play in a two-legged final, the winner of which is crowned National First Division Champion, and gains automatic promotion to the Premier Soccer League for the next season. The loser of the final, along with the teams which came second in their streams, and the 15th placed PSL team, go into the PSL promotion play-offs. The two teams finishing in last place in their streams are automatically relegated to the Vodacom League. They are replaced by the finalists of the [[Vodacom]] League championship game.{{citation needed|date=September 2017}}\n\n==Club and stadium information==\n'''Coastal Stream (excl. Northern Cape):'''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|- \n! width=150|Club\n! width=125|Location\n! width=100|Province\n! width=200|Stadium\n! width=50 |Capacity\n|-\n| [[African Warriors]] || [[Phuthaditjhaba]] || [[Free State (South African province)|Free State]] || [[Charles Mopeli Stadium]] || {{Nts|35000}}\n|-\n| [[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]] || [[Port Elizabeth]] || [[Eastern Cape]] || [[Gelvandale Stadium]] || {{Nts|3000}}\n|-\n| [[Blackburn Rovers FC (South Africa)|Blackburn Rovers]] || [[East London, Eastern Cape|East London]] || [[Eastern Cape]] || [[Buffalo City Stadium]] || {{Nts|16000}}\n|-\n| [[Carara Kicks]] || [[Welkom]] || [[Free State (South African province)|Free State]] || [[Goble Park]] || {{Nts|20000}}\n|-\n| [[FC Cape Town]] || [[Parow, Cape Town|Cape Town <small>(Parow)</small>]] || [[Western Cape]] || [[NNK Rugby Stadium]] || {{Nts|5000}}\n|-\n| [[Hanover Park F.C.|Hanover Park]] || [[Wynberg, Cape Town|Cape Town <small>(Wynberg)</small>]] || [[Western Cape]] || [[Wynberg Military Base Stadium]] || {{Nts|2,500}}\n|-\n| [[Nathi Lions]] || [[KwaMashu|Durban <small>(KwaMashu)</small>]] || [[KwaZulu-Natal]] || [[Princess Magogo Stadium]] || {{Nts|12000}}\n|-\n| [[Thanda Royal Zulu]] || [[Richards Bay]] || [[KwaZulu-Natal]] || [[Richards Bay Stadium]] || {{Nts|8000}}\n|}\n'''Inland Stream (incl. Northern Cape):'''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|- \n! width=150|Club\n! width=125|Location\n! width=100|Province\n! width=200|Stadium\n! width=50 |Capacity\n|-\n| [[Batau F.C.|Batau]] || [[Ermelo, Mpumalanga|Ermelo]] || [[Mpumalanga]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|-\n| [[Black Leopards F.C.|Black Leopards]] || [[Thohoyandou]] || [[Limpopo]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|-\n| [[Dynamos F.C. (South Africa)|Dynamos]] || [[Polokwane]] || [[Limpopo]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|-\n| [[F.C. Aziz Kara|FC AK]] || [[Johannesburg]] || [[Gauteng]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|-\n| [[Jomo Cosmos]] || [[Johannesburg]] || [[Gauteng]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|-\n| [[University of Pretoria F.C.|University of Pretoria]] || [[Pretoria]] || [[Gauteng]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|-\n| [[United FC (South Africa)|United]] || [[Kimberley, Northern Cape|Kimberley]] || [[Northern Cape]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|-\n| [[Witbank Spurs]] || [[Witbank]] || [[Mpumalanga]] || Stadium || {{Nts|}}\n|}\n{{location map+ |South Africa |float=left |width=625 |caption=Location of teams in the '''2010\u201311 National First Division'''. |places=\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-28.580697 |long=28.83203 |label=<small>'''[[African Warriors|Warriors]]</small>''' |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-33.914 |long=25.560 |label=<small>'''[[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]]</small>''' |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-33.0067921 |long=27.9054451 |label=<small>'''[[Blackburn Rovers FC (South Africa)|Blackburn]]</small>''' |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-28.231667 |long=28.305 |label=<small>'''[[Carara Kicks]]</small>''' |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-33.893841 |long=18.583025 |label=<small>'''[[FC Cape Town|Cape Town]]</small>''' |position=right}}\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-34.009003 |long=18.460894 |label=<small>'''[[Hanover Park F.C.|Hanover Park]]</small>''' |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-29.744249 |long=30.971264 |label=<small>'''[[Nathi Lions]]</small>''' |position=left}}\n{{location map~ |South Africa |mark=City locator 15.svg |lat=-28.743392 |long=32.055874 |label=<small>'''[[Thanda Royal Zulu|Thanda Royal]]</small>''' |position=left}}\n}}\n{{Clear}}\n\n==League Standings==\n\n===Coastal Stream===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|Pos|Position}}<br>\n!width=140{{!}}Team\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|Pld|Played}}<br>\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|W|Won}}<br>\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}<br>\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}<br>\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}<br>\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}<br>\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|GD|Goal difference}}<br>\n!width=28{{!}}{{Tooltip|Pts|Points}}<br>\n!Promotion or Relegation\n|- style=\"background:#D0F0C0;\"\n||1||align=\"left\"|[[Bay United F.C.|Bay United]]\n|21||11||7||3||29||13||+16||'''40'''||[[National First Division|NFD]] Coastal Stream Champions 2010/2011\n|- style=\"background:#97DEFF;\"\n||2||align=\"left\"|[[Thanda Royal Zulu F.C.|Thanda Royal Zulu]]\n|21||12||3||6||38||27||+11||'''39'''||Qualification for PSL prom